Sir, I know you have a breast-plate rich enough of your owne, yet to set an higher rate upon your counsels, bee pleased to let these holy jewels of Gods Word (which will bee a bright Urim and Thummim to your bosom
         •
      ) have a place, and that I may be just to the brevity I professe in my Booke, I hasten to bee as I am ever bound, Sir,
